OL,3,CJersey gender pay gap narrows but men
OL,4,Cstill earn 7.8% more
OL,6,FMen are still paid 7.8% more than
OL,7,Fwomen, according to Statistics Jersey.
OL,9,FThis figure covers the gender pay gap
OL,10,F12-month average up to June 2024 and
OL,11,Fmeans a male employee receives #12.40
OL,12,Fmore for an eight-hour work day than
OL,13,Ftheir female colleague.
OL,15,FIt is better than the previous 12-
OL,16,Fmonth average up to June 2023 of 9%,
OL,17,Fbut there have been months since when
OL,18,Fthe difference was larger.
OL,20,FThe most recent data for just June
OL,21,F2024 shows the gap at 6.3%.
